you've got a friend ♪

15:40.504 --> 15:45.205
♪ That's how you know
you've got a friend ♪

15:45.335 --> 15:46.946
♪ Someone who loves you

15:47.076 --> 15:50.601
♪ and makes time
to spend with you ♪

15:50.732 --> 15:54.388
♪ That's how you know
you've got a friend ♪

15:54.518 --> 15:58.000
- ♪ A friend is someone that
you always can count on ♪

15:58.131 --> 16:01.221
- ♪ The way that
I count on you ♪

16:01.351 --> 16:03.049
- ♪ Oh

16:03.179 --> 16:05.051
♪ And if they're
warm and kind ♪

16:05.181 --> 16:07.357
- ♪ Seems they can
read your mind ♪

16:07.488 --> 16:10.578
both: ♪ And hey, if they feel
the same way too ♪

16:10.708 --> 16:14.321
♪ That's how you know
you've got a friend ♪

16:14.451 --> 16:18.151
♪ That's how you know
you've got a friend ♪

16:18.281 --> 16:19.413
- Whoo!

16:19.543 --> 16:21.067
♪ Someone who loves you

16:21.197 --> 16:24.940
♪ and makes time
to spend with you ♪

16:25.071 --> 16:27.987
- ♪ That's how you know
you've got a friend ♪

16:28.117 --> 16:31.468
- ♪ That's how you know
you've got a friend ♪

16:31.599 --> 16:38.301
- ♪ That's how you know
you've got a friend ♪

16:38.432 --> 16:40.869
- [howls]

16:41.000 --> 16:44.220
- I promise to listen to you
from now on, KC.

16:44.351 --> 16:47.484
And that starts now,
with no more hair bows.

16:47.615 --> 16:49.747
[grunts]
- [laughs]

16:49.878 --> 16:52.446
- That's good news, Lacey,
because I want us

16:52.576 --> 16:55.275
to be best friends again, too.

16:55.405 --> 16:58.930
- Uh, bad news,
that wasn't KC's hair bow

16:59.061 --> 17:00.845
Lacey threw out of the window.

17:00.976 --> 17:04.066
It was the ribbon
I keep my keys on.

17:04.197 --> 17:07.330
- So we're all locked in?

17:07.461 --> 17:08.984
- Oops.

17:12.031 --> 17:17.384
[all grunting]

17:17.514 --> 17:21.083
- The door isn't budging.
We're stuck.

17:21.214 --> 17:26.567
- Sunny, you know how you
always say to never give up?

17:26.697 --> 17:27.829
- Um...

17:27.959 --> 17:30.266
- Well, I think
we should give up.

17:30.397 --> 17:32.703
- We just need
to change plan A...

17:32.834 --> 17:34.140
[gasps]

17:36.533 --> 17:39.319
...to Plan B!
Scratch, does that air duct

17:39.449 --> 17:41.277
lead outside?
- Yes.

17:41.408 --> 17:45.151
But it's too high to reach,
and too small.

17:45.281 --> 17:47.762
- You've got a Plan C,
right, Sunny?

17:47.892 --> 17:50.852
- Why don't we try the window?
- I could try to dig us out.

17:50.982 --> 17:52.332
- What about we shout
really loudly...

17:52.462 --> 17:56.205
[overlapping chatter]

17:56.336 --> 18:00.166
- Um, I got an idea.
Uh, hello, hi?

18:00.296 --> 18:03.560
If you'd just listen,
I really think--

18:03.691 --> 18:06.085
Oh, what's the use?
No one's listening.

18:06.215 --> 18:09.914
- [whistles]
Everyone has to be quiet.

18:10.045 --> 18:13.657
KC has an idea,
and we need to listen.

18:13.788 --> 18:17.139
- [giggles]
Well, thanks, Lacey.

18:17.270 --> 18:19.010
Here's my idea.

18:19.141 --> 18:22.013
I'm small enough to
squeeze through that air duct.

18:22.144 --> 18:25.539
Then I crawl out the
other side, and get the keys.

18:25.669 --> 18:27.802
- That's a great idea, KC!

18:27.932 --> 18:30.587
But how will you get
down the other side?

18:30.718 --> 18:32.546
- Don't worry,
I can help with that.

18:32.676 --> 18:35.070
Let's see.

18:35.201 --> 18:37.986
Perfect, I can use
my extra strong ribbons

18:38.117 --> 18:39.944
to make you a harness.

18:40.075 --> 18:42.773
That way, we can lower you
safely down the other side.

18:42.904 --> 18:45.559
[upbeat music]

18:45.689 --> 18:47.996
- What do you
want me to do, KC?

18:48.127 --> 18:51.217
- I need you to lift me up!
- Can do.

18:51.347 --> 18:54.220
[upbeat music]

18:54.350 --> 18:56.570
♪

18:56.700 --> 18:59.616
One, two, three, and up.

18:59.747 --> 19:01.966
Go KC!

19:02.097 --> 19:03.968
But also, be careful!

19:04.099 --> 19:06.884
♪

19:07.015 --> 19:09.844
- That's it, that's it.

19:12.020 --> 19:14.588
Oh, yeah!
[all cheer]

19:14.718 --> 19:18.026
all: Huh?
- Hey, where'd she go?

19:18.157 --> 19:20.985
- KC, come back!
- KC?

19:21.116 --> 19:23.249
KC?
- Where are you?

19:23.379 --> 19:25.599
- [muffled]
I'm right here.

19:25.729 --> 19:29.080
- But, but, how'd you get in?

19:29.211 --> 19:31.387
- I walked through there.

19:31.518 --> 19:33.302
- You could get
in and out all along?

19:33.433 --> 19:37.001
Why didn't you say?
- You didn't ask.

19:39.221 --> 19:41.789
[all cheering]
- We're free!

19:41.919 --> 19:45.836
- Thanks to KC!
That's my best friend.

19:45.967 --> 19:48.796
[joyous music]

19:48.926 --> 19:51.015
♪

19:51.146 --> 19:52.321
- Yay.
- Whoo-hoo!

19:52.452 --> 19:54.454
[laughing]

19:55.759 --> 19:57.239
- One of your other dog friends

19:57.370 --> 19:59.589
might need this
more than I do now.

19:59.720 --> 20:02.113
- Uh, thanks, KC?

20:02.244 --> 20:04.246
[joyous musical flourish]

20:04.377 --> 20:08.207
- Just so you know, you'd make
a pretty good best friend.

20:08.337 --> 20:11.035
- Huh, really?

20:11.166 --> 20:13.560
Uh, thanks.

20:13.690 --> 20:16.302
[upbeat music]

20:16.432 --> 20:18.913
- I've definitely
learned my lesson, KC.

20:19.043 --> 20:21.394
I'll never forget
to listen to you again.

20:21.524 --> 20:24.832
- Thanks, Lacey.
Um, Lacey?

20:24.962 --> 20:27.400
- Yep, you have
my complete attention.

20:27.530 --> 20:29.880
I'm going to be
the best listener ever.

20:30.011 --> 20:31.882
- Lacey!
- Huh?

20:32.013 --> 20:33.841
- Yoo-hoo!

20:33.971 --> 20:36.844
- [chuckles]
I'll keep practicing.

20:36.974 --> 20:38.933
[all laugh]

20:39.063 --> 20:42.241
[upbeat music]

20:42.371 --> 20:44.025
- Uh-huh.

20:44.155 --> 20:45.548
Round brush, please.

20:45.679 --> 20:49.813
- Ooh, that tickles!
[giggles]

20:49.944 --> 20:50.988
- Got it.

20:53.600 --> 20:57.343
- I'm so happy,
I can't keep my paws still.

20:57.473 --> 20:58.953
- I can't wait another minute!

20:59.083 --> 21:01.869
- Then it's a good thing
I'm all done, Doodle.

21:01.999 --> 21:06.090
Meet KC, now with the
poodle puffs she always wanted.

21:06.221 --> 21:08.397
- Look!
Oh, ooh, oh, ohh.

21:08.528 --> 21:12.445
My hair moves when I do!
[giggles], yay!

21:12.575 --> 21:14.795
- [giggles]
Perfect!

21:14.925 --> 21:18.842
- Bouncy and bow-free!
- What do you think, Lacey?

21:18.973 --> 21:20.931
- Hmm.

21:21.062 --> 21:23.630
[tense music]

21:23.760 --> 21:27.286
I love it!

21:27.416 --> 21:30.724
But more importantly,
what do you think, KC?

21:30.854 --> 21:33.814
- That it's just what I wanted.

21:33.944 --> 21:37.426
- Then that's definitely one
for the Style Files.

21:41.604 --> 21:43.650
- Hi, it's me, Sunny,

21:43.780 --> 21:46.130
with another look
inside the Style Files.

21:46.261 --> 21:50.744
What an amazing poodle style!
Wow!

21:50.874 --> 21:54.269
For this hairstyle and more,
check out Sunny's Style Files

21:54.400 --> 21:57.664
at nickjr.com
and the Nick Jr. App.

21:57.794 --> 22:01.102
Keep smiling, keep styling!
[giggles]
